File: South Africa's Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane. AFP/Phill Magakoe  JOHANNESBURG - Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane is urging President Cyril Ramaphosa to step away from efforts to remove her from office. Mkhwebane responded to the President through a letter from her lawyers. READ: Mkhwebane given 10 days to defend herself against suspension Mkhwebane says the President is not legally entitled or competent to take any steps against her. She accused Ramaphosa of being personally, heavily and multiply conflicted in the matter. She says the President's letter to her is unlawful unconstitutional and must be withdrawn.  4_5899922675307908477 by eNCA.com on Scribd  Advocate Busisiwe Mkhwebane's letter to the President by eNews Channel Africa on Scribd 